Package task2

Class FindPrimeNumbers

java.lang.Object
task2.FindPrimeNumbers
class FindPrimeNumbers extends Object
The FindPrimeNumbers class implements the Eratosthenes sieve algorithm for finding prime numbers without division and getting the remainder from division and prints the found prime numbers.

    • createArrayOfNumbers

      static int[] createArrayOfNumbers()
      Creates array of integers filled with consecutive positive values in the range from 1 to 300.
      Returns:
      array of integers filled with consecutive positive values.

    • findPrimeNumbers

      static void findPrimeNumbers(int[] newArray)
      Finds prime numbers in the range from 1 to 300 by the Eratosthenes Sieve algorithm. The newArray array is filled with consecutive positive integer numbers and numbers that are not prime are replaced with the -1 value.
      Parameters:
      newArray - array of integers filled with consecutive positive values that must be sorted.

    • printPrimeNumbers

      static void printPrimeNumbers(int[] newArray)
      Prints the prime numbers as formatted text. The -1 values in the newArray array are not printed.
      Parameters:
      newArray - sorted array of prime numbers.

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      Calls static methods of the FindPrimeNumbers class to find and print prime numbers. The args are not used.
      Parameters:
      args - command-line arguments.
